The paper discusses the performance evaluation and dimensioning of a virtualized mobility management entity (vMME) for 5G mobile networks. This involves modeling and analyzing the queuing network of the vMME in a data center, estimating the overall mean system delay and signaling workload, and conducting scalability analysis. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). 

The paper also considers the data center setup and billing model, which suggests a possible fit with cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of analytic expressions and simulation for performance evaluation and dimensioning may also relate to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves modeling and analysis of a specific system, which could be relevant to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
